<br>
I know the idea of autotraining is to prevent someone from gimping their character but I don't think those few extra points will have much of an effect. Autotraining is only used now for people to get those few extra free points of training (autotraining an assassin's stealth while powerleveling).<br>
<br>
As for elven blademasters, I think they would make a really good piercemaster or shieldmaster, but not as good blade or bluntmaster.  <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Raeloran Twinblade</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, 50 Blademaster, Legendary Grandmaster Armorcrafter, Pellinor</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=theravensclaw>The Ravens Claw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#000000>(6/4/03 5:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=110.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://avatars.cheetachat.com/img_ava/redmage.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Maybe I'm just stupid(probably am)&gt;.&gt;</span><hr size=1> Statistically, yes, elves do make the worst blunt or blademaster, but elven BMs and nearly identical to saracen mercs except for 5 point lower dex, 10 point lower STR and Con and 15 point high qui.  All of the Stat difference can be easily remedied with the starting points.<br>
<br>
But my weird little theory wasn't about stats, it was about common sense and all the fluff.  BM's are graceful fighters that attack quickly, if not very strongly.  Elves are graceful creatures and might utilize 2 weapons to make up for their lack of strength, thus becoming the first BM's.<br>
<br>
